At 4-2 entering their bye week, the Giants place among the elite in the NFC is debatable. 
But they've been pretty dominant when it comes to conference player of the week awards. 
Ahmad Bradshaw is the latest Giants to win the honor. 
He was named NFC Player of the Week on Tuesday after scoring three one-yard touchdowns and 104 yards on 26 carries in the Giants' 27-24 Week 6 win over Buffalo. 
Bradshaw's 30-yard run helped set up Lawrence Tynes game-winning 23-yard field with 1:32 remaining.
Overall, Bradshaw leads the Giants with 390 rushing yards and five touchdowns. He is the second Giant to win the award in the season's first six weeks. 
Eli Manning was named NFC Offensive Player of the Week after a dominant performance in a win over Philadelphia in Week 3. 
Bradshaw previously received the award last year after running for 129 yards and a touchdown in a Week 4 win over the Bears.
